{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Mold"], "type": "title", "extent": [59, 68], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [68, 105], "text": ["Simulates anti-aliased mold."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [105, 149], "text": ["This operator simulates anti-aliased mold."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [149, 275], "text": ["You will first generate a material that outputs a color, then pipe its\noutput into the Surface Color input of this operator."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [275, 685], "text": ["The Mold Threshold (", {"text": ["mthresh"], "type": "code"}, ") input controls the contribution of the\nrotting agents, and represents a good candidate for animation at the\nshader level if tied to a ", {"text": ["Parameter"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/parameter", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/parameter"}, " operator. The lower the ", {"text": ["mthresh"], "type": "code"}, "\nvalue, the greater the overall moldy area. To increase the percentage of\ncore mold in the overall moldy area, bump up the value of the Core Mold\nAmplifier (", {"text": ["coremult"], "type": "code"}, ") parameter."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [685, 1329], "text": ["If the Surface Position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, "), Normal Vector (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") and Surface Color (", {"text": ["Cf"], "type": "code"}, ")\ninputs are not connected, the global variables by the same name will be\nused instead. Typically, you will use ", {"text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, "\nas inputs for ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ", and any operator that yields a lit color, such as\n", {"text": ["Shiny Metal"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/shinymetal"}, " or ", {"text": ["Lighting Model"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}, ", as inputs for ", {"text": ["Cf"], "type": "code"}, ". You will not need to\ntouch ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " unless you wish to apply additional displacement to the mold.\nIf you need to access the global variables directly, they are available\nfrom the ", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1338, 1362], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/banana", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/banana"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1362, 1388], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cavities", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/cavities"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1388, 1412], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1412, 1438], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1438, 1461], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/rust", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/rust"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1329, 1338], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates anti-aliased mold."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "mold", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/mold"}, "title": ["Mold"]}